{"id":"2004.02090","submitter":"Fei Xu","authors":"Fei Xu and Yang Zhang","title":"On indefinite and potentially universal quadratic forms over number\n  fields","comments":"18 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A number field $k$ admits a binary integral quadratic form which represents\nall integers locally but not globally if and only if the class number of $k$ is\nbigger than one. In this case, there are only finitely many classes of such\nbinary integral quadratic forms over $k$. A number field $k$ admits a ternary\nintegral quadratic form which represents all integers locally but not globally\nif and only if the class number of $k$ is even. In this case, there are\ninfinitely many classes of such ternary integral quadratic forms over $k$. An\nintegral quadratic form over a number field $k$ with more than one variables\nrepresents all integers of $k$ over the ring of integers of a finite extension\nof $k$ if and only if this quadratic form represents $1$ over the ring of\nintegers of a finite extension of $k$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 Apr 2020 04:15:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 May 2020 03:30:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 1 Nov 2021 03:26:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-02"}
